The `height` and `maxHeight` were both set to the same value (`89vh`), which is a common pattern when you want a flex container to fill available space but still respect a ceiling. Setting both to `85vh` means the panel will always render at exactly 85% of the viewport height, with internal content scrolling via `overflow: hidden` on the outer shell and per-section scroll areas inside. The 4vh reduction (~35px on a 1080p display) gives more breathing room between the panel and viewport edges.
